  {
    "type": "EXEGETICAL (ORIGINAL LANGUAGES)",
    "name": "Cambridge Bible for Schools and Colleges",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "29",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "when he reigned,",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " that ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "he smote",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "] R.V. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "that as soon as he was king he smote",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". Being an usurper he would desire to make his power secure by removing at once everyone who might become a rival. This is expressed in the original, and the R.V. seems to bring it out fully. Thus God used the policy of Baasha to fulfil the prophecy against Jeroboam.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "by his servant",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "] The Hebrew says ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "by the hand of his servant",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", and as this mode of expression is not uncommon in the Old Testament, the R.V. has given the full form. For the threat against Jeroboam and the reason, see ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "1 Kings 14:9-11",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ".",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "EXEGETICAL (ORIGINAL LANGUAGES)",
    "name": "Pulpit Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_sub_title",
        "text": "Verse 29.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " - ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "And it cams to pass, when he reigned, that he smote all the house of Jeroboam; he left not to Jeroboam any that breathed",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " [Same expression in ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Joshua 11:14",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; cf. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Deuteronomy 20:16",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". Males and females alike were destroyed; see ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "1 Kings 14:11",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "], ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "until he had destroyed him according unto the saying of the Lord, which he spake by his servant AhiJah the Shilonite",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " [",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "1 Kings 14:10",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". It is not implied that it was ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "because",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " of this prophecy that Baasha exterminated the house of Jeroboam. It is probable that, so far from setting himself to fulfil it, he knew nothing about it, and, as he thought, merely took effectual measures for his own security. His seat could never be safe, so long as one of Jeroboam's house survived. Grotius aptly cites, with reference to these wholesale murders, the saying, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greek",
        "text": "ο{ς πατέρα κτείνας υἱοὺς",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greek",
        "text": "κατέλιπε",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "]: 1 Kings 15:29",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "EXEGETICAL (ORIGINAL LANGUAGES)",
    "name": "Keil and Delitzsch Biblical Commentary on the Old Testament",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "He walked in the ways of his father (Jeroboam) and in his sin, i.e., in the calf-worship introduced by Jeroboam (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "1 Kings 12:28",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "). When Nadab in the second year of his reign besieged Gibbethon, which the Philistines and occupied, Baasha the son of Ahijah, of the house, I the family or tribe, of Issachar, conspired against him and slew him, and after he became king exterminated the whole house of Jeroboam, without leaving a single soul, whereby the prediction of the prophet Ahijah (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "1 Kings 14:10",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ".) was fulfilled. Gibbethon, which was allotted to the Danites (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Joshua 19:44",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "), has not yet been discovered. It probably stood close to the Philistian border, and was taken by the Philistines, from whom the Israelites attempted to wrest it by siege under both Nadab and Baasha (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "1 Kings 16:16",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "), though apparently without success. לא השׁאיר כּל־נשׁמה as in ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Joshua 11:14",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " (see the Comm. on ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Deuteronomy 20:16",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ").",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  }
]